Usage: savePtnPin [-help] <fileName> { -ptn <string> | -all  | -design  | -selected  }

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
<fileName>              # Specifies the name of the file in which the partition
                        # pin assignment information will be saved.
                        # (string, required)
-all                    # Specifies that pin assignment information will be
                        # saved for all partitions, including the top-level
                        # design. (bool, optional)
-design                 # Specifies that pin assignment information will be
                        # saved only for the top-level design. (bool, optional)
-ptn <string>           # Specifies name of the partition for which the pin
                        # assignment information is to be saved (string, optional)
-selected               # Specifies that pin assignment information will be
                        # saved for all the selected pins of partitions,
                        # including the top-level design. (bool, optional)